rComments: Meetings are useless, doesn't give valuable input. Is pretty judgemental, makes a lot of faces when reading/listening to students' work. Assignment/exercise instructions are extremely unclear and class is very disorganized. Never enjoyed going to lecture. Made me hate writing.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lots of homework', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Prof Waterman is pretty unapproachable. She seems like she subtly hates you if you don't participate in class. Her instructions are very unclear and vague. She'll also destroy your work.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: This class is very dependent on attendance and completion of long tedious homework assignments. Laurel's lectures are fun, however she grades very harshly and offers minimal feedback with respect to the amount of work applied. Be warned that no grades will be given until well past the drop date.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader', 'Participation matters']

rComments: I've had Laurel a bunch of times because I'm in the PWC program. She's a hard marker, for sure. But it doesn't mean that you can't do well in this course.  She's a very genuine, interesting lecturer. And she gives lots of opportunity to meet with her outside of class during her office hours.   Truly enjoyed my 2 years of classes with her.
Really good prof. Marks kinda hard though, but still it's worth it. Kinda hot too.

I didn't go into this expecting an easy course but there's no way to get an A. We write about personal stories yet she graded my final portfolio a B because the stories I chose weren't "interesting enough". This course is mandatory to get into the WRI program and I lost big marks because my life wasn't terrible? I know I write good fiction...

Compared to other professors in this program, her helpfulness is minimal to you writing better. The personal interviews are not nearly as useful or constructive as, say, Price's or Curry's. She talks in circles and changes her mind. She is not very organized and is vague when it comes to her expectations.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Gives lots of homework exercises that are very time consuming, unnecessarily hard marker, vague expectations, vague lectures, limited feedback (only on one assignment the whole term), wouldn't take her again.

I think I could have done a lot better in this class if there was more feedback. We only got two assignments (out of sooo many) back throughout the entire semester. Writing the stories was fun and the lectures helped. There was a lot of homework but if your enjoy writing, you're good.

She helped improve my writing skills tremendously. However, she only gave us feedback on one assignment, the midterm, which made it very difficult to understand how to improve. Lectures were important but  I thought her grading was far too harsh and her expectation too high.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: If you really want a 4.0 in this class, prepare to work for it. Definitely NOT a bird course. Long and pointless exercises are aplenty! Also, be prepared to print a ton of exercises, she wants them handed in hard-copy every class. Get comfortable reading  out your exercises in front of the class, she'll make you go in order. Buy the course pack.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Worst prof because she marks so so so hard. I took this course as a GPA boost and the class average was only a 60. She gets you to do pointless exercises every week and the assignments are boring, non fiction and unimaginative-hardly "expressive writing". Avoid at all costs, she destroyed my average last year!

She was very approachable when it came to asking questions, but she got some sick fun out of putting people on the spot in class with her pointless exercises... the course is called expressive writing yet all of the assignments were the SAME (non fiction no imagination!). She marks pointlessly hard. AVOID IF POSSIBLE!!!

Great professor. Don't come to class expecting a 4.0 (or a 3.7) if you're not willing to work extremely hard for it. Attend all lectures and participate multiple times per class. The class was enjoyable though I probably wouldn't retake it as her expectations are vague.
Lovely woman but seemed a bit hard when it came to marking our papers.
very very tough marker, although helpful
Very helpful and inspiring. Always showed interest and enjoyment in reading her student's assignments. Never hesitated to thoroughly edit the drafts.
A very friendly and helpful prof. I did well in her class.
Very understanding prof! Really like her!
HOTTTIEEEE!!!!!!
